foia:ProcessedRequestSection.foia:FootnoteText: Some bureaus made entries in FY 16 that resulted in minor adjustments to the number of requests they had pending at the start of the fiscal year. Additionally, under DOI’s existing Electronic FOIA Tracking System validation processes, the total number of perfected requests may vary from the total number of processed requests (due to this, there are fewer perfected requests being captured in the section VII.C charts than are being captured in this chart). DOI continues to review its processes and will make any necessary adjustments in FY 17.

Due to a regulatory change, OIG began processing appeals arising from its own FOIA responses partway through the fiscal year, including new appeals and existing appeals referred to OIG by FOIA/PA Appeals.
